ggle to achieve common goals. Union Power traces the evidence of these twin concepts through the history of the Niagara region’s labour movement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aLabor movement -- Ontario -- Niagara Peninsula -- History. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh1 aSavage, Larry, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012z978311127413308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012z978311127716540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781926836799423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781926836799/original  a978-3-11-127413-3  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-127716-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2012b2012  aGBV-deGruyter-alles